{
  "title": "ISic001155. Funerary inscription for Gaios Seios Ptolemaios",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Γάιε Σήιε \n                    Πτολεμαῖε \n                    Σαμαρεῦ\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Γάιε\">Γάιε</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σήιε\">Σήιε</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Πτολεμαῖε\">Πτολεμαῖε</span>  <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"Σαμαρεῦ\">Σαμαρεῦ</span></span>  <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\">χαῖρε</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Γάιε Σήιε \n                    Πτολεμαῖε \n                    Σαμαρεῦ\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Γάιε\">ΓΑΙΕ</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σήιε\">ΣΗΙΕ</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Πτολεμαῖε\">ΠΤΟΛΕΜΑΙΕ</span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"Σαμαρεῦ\">ΣΑΜΑΡΕΥ</span></span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001155_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo civico di Termini Imerese\" src=\"ISic001155_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001155.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo civico di Termini Imerese\" src=\"ISic001155-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text from autopsy</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou</a></p>  <p>Gaios Seios Ptolemaios of Samaria, farewell.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Gaios and Seios derive from the Latin praenomen Gaius and nomen Seius. Gaius is very common, and Seius is well-attested in Sicily, beginning in the first century CE (see RPC 1.670 and <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000539\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000539</a>). As argued by Brugnone (1974) Samareus is an ethnic, cf. Roberts (1969 no.369). Brugnone (1974) also suggests that the connection between the name Ptolemy and Samaria is not surprising, as Ptolemaic Egypt had an interest in Samaria.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 1969.0369 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282</a></li><li> 506 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001116\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001116</a></li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">336</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a></li><li> Brugnone 1974 6 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397</a></li><li> Noy 1993 no.161 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000166\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000166</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Greek text is straight, with crisp and well-defined letter forms. Extremely regular in layout and in spaces between letters. Serifs used on most letters. The middle lines of epsilons are formed as right-pointing triangles, but in line 4 is formed as an arrow instead. Broken-bar alphas are used throughout.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.4.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.4</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.5.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.5</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.6.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.6</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Η-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Η type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ι-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ι type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Λ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Λ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ tyoe3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Χ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Χ type3</a> </p> Line 1  33  Line 2  29-33  Lines 3-4  33-38  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
